citation.case_name: Webb C. Hayes, Plintiff in Error v. The Hocking Valley Railway Company

html:
249 U.S. 591

39 S.Ct. 389

63 L.Ed. 792

Webb C. HAYES, plintiff in error,
v.
The HOCKING VALLEY RAILWAY COMPANY.

No. 388.

Supreme Court of the United States

April 28, 1919

Mr. Chas. A. Seiders, of Toledo, Ohio, for plaintiff in error.

Messrs. John F. Wilson, of Columbus, Ohio, and Lloyd T. Williams, of Toledo, Ohio (Messrs. Wilson & Rector, of Columbus, Ohio, and Brown, Geddes, Schmettau & Williams, of Toledo, Ohio, of counsel), for defendant in error.

PER CURIAM.

1

Dismissed for want of jurisdiction upon the authority of Farrell v. O'Brien, 199 U. S. 89, 100, 25 Sup. Ct. 727, 50 L. Ed. 101; Empire State-Idaho Mining Co. v. Hanley, 205 U. S. 225, 232, 27 Sup. Ct. 476, 51 L. Ed. 779; Goodrich v. Ferris, 214 U. S. 71, 79, 29 Sup. Ct. 580, 53 L. Ed. 914; Brolan v. United States, 236 U. S. 216, 218, 35 Sup. Ct. 285, 59 L. Ed. 544.
